race.comment: Much of the race centres around the SUSHI EXPRESS form but going with KALIUWAA FALLS (4) who could be over the odds. Has raced twice at listed level this time in, finishing fifth at both, the latest in the Tasmania Stakes. The extra trip is a plus and fitter again. Has a good record course and distance and leading rider stays aboard. Looks set to improve sharply third run in. EARENDEL (8) was a close-up fourth behind Sunshine Express here over 1650m last time out. Probably has the most upside of this field and better off at the draw can turn the tables. THE LONGEST YARD (12) was just edged out in the same race when runner-up and is a super consistent type drawn well and should be in the finish again. BLONDE STAR (6) went close last time behind SUSHI EXPRESS and continues to race well. Tricky gate but among the chances. SUSHI EXPRESS (1) beat them all last time fair and square but does have a tricky gate to overcome.
